At least one group of online hacktivists claimed responsibility for the NSA website being downed by a DSD attack.
DSD attacks are designed to flood a targeted site until the servers are overloaded and the site collapses.
The cyber tactics are not very sophisticated and the attacks are not intended to penetrate the internal network of the targeted system.
The formerly top-secret NSA, once nicknamed the  No Such Agency , has come under the spotlight and been heavily criticized in recent months following a wave of revelations about its vast communications surveillance programs at home and abroad  which are part of the secret NSA files stolen from the agency and leaked by disgruntled former NSA consultant Edward Snowden.
