 We aspire to a better tomorrow, a new Egypt and a second republic , President Morsi said during the solemn ceremony broadcast live on public television.
 Today, the Egyptian people have laid the foundations for a new life  absolute freedom, true democracy and stability , explained Mr. Morsi, a 60-year-old US-trained engineer from the Muslim Brotherhood, a fundamentalist group that for more than 84 years since its formation has been considered an illegal organization and harshly repressed by successive governments.
